Product Description

UGREEN Gigabit USB C to Ethernet Adapter

  • Faster and more stable wired network than Wi-Fi.
  • Up to 1000Mbps internet speed.
  • Compatible with most USB C or Thunderbolt 3 devices.
  • Stylish and Durable aluminum shell.
  • Compact and Portable Size.

Read more

Systems Supported:

  • Driver free on Windows 10/8.1/8, Mac OS, Chrome OS, iPad OS, and Android.
  • Driver needed on Windows 7/XP/Vista and Linux. (you can easily install the driver through our instructions.)
  • Compatible with Nintendo Switch, the game console should update to the latest version 10.1.0.

Compatibility List (Partial):

USB C (Thunderbolt 3) Laptops:

  • Compatible with MacBook Pro 16''/15”/13'' (M1/2020/2019/2018/2017/2016), MacBook (2019/2018/2017/2016/2015), MacBook Air 13” (M1/2020/2018), iMac Pro, iMac 2021 M1, iMac models from 2017, Mac mini 2018
  • Compatible with Microsoft Surface Pro 7/Surface Laptop 3/Surface Book 2/Surface Go; Google Chromebook Pixel (2015)/ Pixelbook/ Pixel Slate
  • Compatible with Dell XPS 13/15, Latitude 7373/ 5570/ 5490/ 5400(2019); Lenovo Yoga 920/Yoga 720/ThinkPad X1
  • Compatible with ASUS Zenbook 3/U4100/ROG/Chromebook Flip, Alienware 13/15/17; Razor Blade Pro/Stealth, Acer Aspire V Nitro/ Switch Alpha 12
  • Compatible with HP Spectre13/Envy 13/EliteBook/Spectre/Envy X360

USB C Tablets/Phones:

  • Compatible with iPad Pro 2020/2018, iPad Air 4 2020
  • Compatible with Samsung Galaxy Galaxy S20/S20 Plus/S20 Ultra/S10/S10 Plus/S10e/S9/S9 Plus/S8/S8 Plus/Note 10/Note 10+/Note 9/ Note 8, Samsung Tab Pro Google Pixel, Pixel 2, Pixel C, Nexus 5X / 6P, Lumia 950 / 950XL
  • Compatible with Huawei P40/P40 Pro/Mate 30/Mate 30 Pro; Xiaomi Mi 10 Pro

Package Included:

  • USB C to Ethernet Gigabit Adapter x 1
  • User Manual x1

1000Mbps Hyper Speed

With the stable wired connection, this USB C to Lan adapter lets you enjoy 1Gbps/1000Mbps Ethernet speed for movie streaming, online gaming, video conferencing, uploading and downloading large files without buffering.

LED Indicator

UGREEN Gigabit USB C to Network Adapter is designed with LED Indicator, you can clearly see the working status of the network card. (Green light Steady: Power, Yellow light Blinks: Data Transfer.)

Compact & Portable Size

UGREEN USB C to Ethernet Adapter has a brand new small size design. You can easily take it anywhere with your briefcase or pocket, very suitable for a business person.

      1.0 out of 5 stars Network adapter driver for OS X Catalina needs work
      Reviewed in the United States on August 22, 2020
      Verified Purchase
      The manufacturer provides a rar archive that you will need to expand. OS X does not include a default rar unarchiver so you'll have to either find one (not hard to do) or use a different operating system that supports expanding rar files. This additional step shouldn't be required to perform a device driver installation. The installation of the latest driver available as of this writing (filename: AX88179_178A_macOS_10.15_above_Driver_Installer_v2.16.0.rar) requires that you allow for a blocked extension in OS X Security & Privacy, which will not work in future versions of OS X. When I emailed UGreen support about the issue, they asked me to contact Amazon rather than providing a properly updated driver. I suggest paying the extra money to get an Apple supported usb-c network adapter. Apple is selling a Belkin usb-c network adapter and Amazon sells one too that I am trying next.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Works Great on my new Windows 10 Laptop
      Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2020
      Verified Purchase
      I recently bought a new Acer Swift 5 laptop that has Windows 10 OS. It has a small footprint, so real estate is at a premium meaning that it was missing a port I really needed - an Ethernet port so I could hook the laptop directly to my Internet modem for maximum download speeds. The built-in wi-fi worked fine, but I really wanted a faster Internet connection. The laptop had 3 USB ports and one was a USB 3.1C Thunderbolt port. So, I looked on Amazon for an adapter that would plug into the laptop's USB Thunderbolt port and give me an Ethernet port on the other end to allow me to connect to my cable modem.

      This adapter stood out because it had the right connectors and was reasonable in cost. When it arrived, I fired up my laptop and plugged the adapter into the laptop and connected my high speed modem, and voila! My laptop recognized my modem instantly, and I was on the Internet with a direct connection allowing me to disable my laptop's wi-fi and triple my download speed.

      Bottom line: I am very happy with this purchase. No drivers to download. Worked instantly out of the box. Appears to be of high quality. 5-stars.

      5.0 out of 5 stars Does what it's supposed to do, reliably
      Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2021
      Verified Purchase
      Macs are finicky to USB network adapters. Amazon can attest to the fact that I tried and returned a half dozen USB-C hubs that failed to maintain a network connection on my MacBook Pro (2019) for more than a couple of days. The connection would just die. This UGREEN adapter does 'hog' an entire Thunderbolt port but it works. Nothing more to say. It's reliable - the connection does not drop - and it's fast - all as advertised. So if you want to reduce WiFi usage in a congested work-and-study-from-home household, this should be your go-to adapter.
